- ts: 2026-04-15T13:08:00Z
  event: clarify_critic
  feature: extract-optional-skills-to-plugin
  findings:
    - "Intent rated HIGH papers over a contradiction in the source — the prompt opens with 'move to a new public repo' and later says 'don't mind if these belong in this repo' and 'separate repo also fine.' Three different answers to 'where do these skills live' in one paragraph."
    - "Intent HIGH rests on an unverified assumption — that Claude Code plugins actually avoid contributing skill descriptions to the system reminder when installed-but-disabled. The user asserted this; the assessment inherited it uncritically. If false, the value collapses and this re-runs #064."
    - "Scope LOW undersells the gap — 'audit which skills are not referenced by lifecycle/overnight/discovery/requirements' is a procedure, not a criterion. 'Referenced' could mean invoked programmatically, listed as a trigger, documented, or 'I use this when doing X' — each yields a different candidate set."
    - "'UI skills' is treated as anchoring a category, but nothing in the source defines the category. statusline is a shell script; insights is analytical. The example may have been gestural ('things like the UI skills'), not categorical."
    - "Requirements HIGH rests on an unquantified value case — #064 established ~2.6k tokens (<2% of context) saved. The assessment treats plugins as a qualitative game-changer without re-quantifying savings under the plugin mechanism."
    - "Assessment imports #064's framing but does not confront direct tension — #064's rationale cited multi-file state coherence as the cost, which is a property of the skills themselves (cross-references, workflow assumptions), not the loading mechanism. Moving skills into a plugin does not dissolve cross-skill references."
    - "The same-repo-plugin vs. separate-repo decision is filed as one of four equivalent ambiguities, but it has downstream architectural consequences (just setup, symlink architecture, /setup-merge responsibilities, fork onboarding) that the list-of-items questions do not."
  dispositions:
    apply: 2
    dismiss: 1
    ask: 4
  applied_fixes:
    - "Added to Research open questions: does the Claude Code plugin system actually gate skill-description loading from the session system reminder, or only gate invocation? (load-bearing for the entire value case)"
    - "Added to Research open questions: does plugin extraction require unwinding cross-skill references in SKILL.md bodies, hook code, or workflow docs, or can plugins coexist with cross-references intact?"
  status: ok
